{
  "texts": [
    "Early stopping is a technique that continuously monitors the model's performance on a separate validation dataset and terminates the training process if the validation loss fails to improve or consistently deteriorates over a predefined number of epochs (five in our case).",
    "In the current work, while the training set was used to update the model parameters, the validation set was used to continuously monitor the model performance on a separate unseen dataset and prevent overfitting the training data.",
    "After approximately 150 epochs, the validation loss stopped improving, and the early stopping mechanism terminated the training.",
    "This approach allowed us to identify the optimal stopping point during training and capture a model that strikes a balance between fitting the training data and generalizing it to unseen data.",
    "At the completion of the training, the MSE values for the training and validation datasets were 0.0146 and 0.0148, respectively."
  ]
}